Money Stuff =0A I have never been to business school, but I gather that a c=
ertain amount of =0Athe curriculum involves pretending to do business stuff=
. You get =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D82588=
1&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12224216&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D010=
62025>=0A=0A=0A=0ASuccessful MBA class project=0A=0AI have never been to bu=
siness school, but I gather that a certain amount of =0Athe curriculum invo=
lves pretending to do business stuff. You get a class =0Aproject that is li=
ke =E2=80=9Ccome up with a good plan to develop this golf resort, =0Abuild =
a financial model, create a PowerPoint deck and do a presentation in =0Acla=
ss describing and arguing for your vision.=E2=80=9D Sometimes the project w=
ill be a =0Apurely invented hypothetical situation, but more often, for rea=
lism, it will be =0Abased on a real case, some real business situation that=
 actually happened. To =0Akeep things relevant, the case might be from quit=
e recent history. To bereally =0Arelevant, and to make it a bit more challe=
nging to find the answers, the case =0Amight be an ongoing situation: =E2=
=80=9CHere is an actual golf resort that is actually =0Ain the early stages=
 of being developed; what=E2=80=99s your plan to do it=3F=E2=80=9D=0A=0AAnd=
