 margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px 5px;">Successful MBA class project</h2> </t=
d> </tr> </table> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have never been to busines=
s school, but I gather that a certain amount of the curriculum involves pre=
tending to do business stuff. You get a class project that is like =E2=80=
=9Ccome up with a good plan to develop this golf resort, build a financial =
model, create a PowerPoint deck and do a presentation in class describing a=
nd arguing for your vision.=E2=80=9D Sometimes the project will be a purely=
 invented hypothetical situation, but more often, for realism, it will be b=
ased on a real case, some real business situation that actually happened. T=
o keep things relevant, the case might be from quite=C2=A0recent history. T=
o be=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>relevant, and to make it a bit more challeng=
ing to find the answers, the case might be an ongoing situation: =E2=80=9CH=
ere is an actual=C2=A0golf resort that is actually in the early stages of b=
eing developed; what=E2=80=99s your plan to do it=3F=E2=80=9D</p> <p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then you form a team with your classmates and pret=
end to develop the golf resort. And you come up with a plan and build a fin=
ancial model. And maybe they are good, and you think =E2=80=9Chuh, this is =
a great opportunity; if we actually developed this golf resort, we could ma=
ke a lot of money.=E2=80=9D And then you finish the project and do the pres=
entation and get an A- and consider a career in golf resort development. Pe=
rhaps when you graduate you even get a job at the company that developed th=
e golf resort you pretended to develop.</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or=
. Or. Or=3F What if you stopped pretending=3F What if the opportunity is t=
oo good=3F What if you and your project team do such a good job pretending =
to develop the golf resort=C2=A0that you just go ahead and develop the golf=
 resort=3F What if, in the course of pretending to develop the golf resort,=
 you build a financial model showing that the opportunity is extremely lucr=
ative=3F What if you create a really compelling vision for how to develop t=
he golf resort=3F What if you contact people who actually work in the golf-=
resort-development industry for their advice on your class presentation, an=
d they are so impressed with your ideas that they want in on the deal=3F Wh=
at if you go and raise actual financing to actually develop the golf resort=
=3F=C2=A0</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What if your plan and financing =
and contacts are so compelling that you are able to=C2=A0<em>jump the origi=
nal deal</em>=3F What if you call up the people who own the land on which t=
he golf resort is going to be developed and say =E2=80=9Clook, I know that =
you are already working with people to develop this golf resort. But we hav=
e done a class project on developing this golf resort, and we think our ide=
as are so good that you should work with us rather than the original people=
.=E2=80=9D What if you=E2=80=99re right=3F What if the people who own the =
land break their deal with the original people and bring you in to develop =
the golf resort=3F</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well then you get an A+=
 in my class, man. That is putting your business education to work. Here=E2=
