=80=9Cloan funds are replacing banks as lenders.=E2=80=9D Rather, it is mor=
e like =E2=80=9Cloan funds are making banks=C2=A0<em>more senior </em>as le=
nders=E2=80=9D: Instead of lending money to a diversified portfolio of risk=
y businesses, banks increasingly lend money to=C2=A0<em>other lenders=C2=A0=
</em>who make those loans. The private credit funds have a senior claim on =
the underlying businesses; the banks then have a senior claim on the privat=
e credit funds=E2=80=99 assets. The banks get paid back in full if the priv=
ate credit funds get paid back in part.=C2=A0</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">The banks, in this hybrid model, don=E2=80=99t put their depositors=E2=
=80=99 money in risk-free assets like Fed reserves. But they put their mone=
y in assets that are somewhat more risk-free than traditional corporate or =
consumer loans, in senior tranches of pools of corporate or consumer loans.=
